From: James Chapman <jchapman@katalix.com>
Date: Thu, 20 Jun 2024 12:22:37 +0100
Subject: l2tp: remove unused list_head member in l2tp_tunnel
Git-commit: a744e2d03a91507646ffff8a03a19a2f34a6798a
Patch-mainline: v6.11-rc1
References: git-fixes

Remove an unused variable in struct l2tp_tunnel which was left behind
by commit c4d48a58f32c5 ("l2tp: convert l2tp_tunnel_list to idr").

Signed-off-by: James Chapman <jchapman@katalix.com>
Reviewed-by: Tom Parkin <tparkin@katalix.com>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Acked-by: Jean Delvare <jdelvare@suse.de>
---
 net/l2tp/l2tp_core.c |    2 --
 net/l2tp/l2tp_core.h |    1 -
 2 files changed, 3 deletions(-)

--- a/net/l2tp/l2tp_core.c
+++ b/net/l2tp/l2tp_core.c
@@ -1456,8 +1456,6 @@ int l2tp_tunnel_create(struct net *net,
 	/* Init delete workqueue struct */
 	INIT_WORK(&tunnel->del_work, l2tp_tunnel_del_work);
 
-	INIT_LIST_HEAD(&tunnel->list);
-
 	err = 0;
 err:
 	if (tunnelp)
--- a/net/l2tp/l2tp_core.h
+++ b/net/l2tp/l2tp_core.h
@@ -177,7 +177,6 @@ struct l2tp_tunnel {
 	enum l2tp_encap_type	encap;
 	struct l2tp_stats	stats;
 
-	struct list_head	list;		/* Keep a list of all tunnels */
 	struct net		*l2tp_net;	/* the net we belong to */
 
 	atomic_t		ref_count;
